file=Brand Studio/weave/operational/commands/weave-commands.md · h=name: weave-commands\ntype: operational/commands\nstatus: consolidated from trigger phrases in weave's skill files — no new triggers invented; precedence rules added where triggers overlap\nassigned_agent: weave (Brand Studio / Storytelling)\ndate_added: 2026-07-07\n · p:=Routing reference for weave: phrase → skill.\n · tb=\| Skill \| Natural-language triggers \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| brand-story-arcs \| "campaign story," "narrative angle," "does this fit our story," "build our brand story," "story continuity" \| `/weave-arc` \| · tb=\| brand-storytelling \| "story structure," "make this story land," "hook for this," "how do I tell this," "make it memorable" \| `/weave-craft` \| · tb=\| (full pipeline) \| any campaign/content needing narrative treatment end-to-end \| `/weave-story` \| · ### Architecture before craft=Campaign-bound story work always runs the arc check first — polishing an off-arc chapter is wasted craft. Standalone craft questions (a talk, a founder post, a pitch moment) run brand-storytelling directly.\n · ### "New story" — arc vs chapter="Build/change our story" → the arc itself (creation loop or operator-owned amendment). "Story for this campaign" → a chapter of the existing arc.\n · ### What weave does NOT take=- Final wording → lena (voice + humanic pass). Weave delivers chapter + craft treatment, not copy.\n- Concept generation and dedupe → muse (weave positions the survivors).\n- Serialization into posts and calendars → pulse.\n- Investor-facing narrative documents → echo (facts must match the arc; contradictions escalate).\n- Persuasion-principle selection → Behavioral Science (cialdini) when built.\n · f:=No clear match → ask: positioning (which chapter) or telling (how it lands)?\n